Lyrics

Mujhe nai karna hai kisko bhi prove 
mujhe pata hai ki kitna hu kabil mei
Meri hai ginti yaha sabse alag 
isiliye toh auro mei hota nai shamil mei 
Aa mil le dekh 
Kitna jeeta hu hip hop ko 
Izzat de baap ko 
Karte hum kaam 
Toh raat ko 
Yaad rakhte batko 
Mil julke rehte chahe 
Koi bhi jaat ho 
Tu karte Reh  dream 
Mei meri team 
Hum seedha kardete dream come true 
Independent ka scene 
Sikhta hardin 
Ratein kali nai 
Ab hai rangeen 
Jitna diya hai abhi sablenge cheen 
Subliminally sab lene lage meaning 
Gane ka 
Karke dikhaneka 
Aise nai bolte ye khel nai dikhave ka 
Kya toh dikhaneka 

Kya toh dikhaneka sab kuch tum dekhrele 
Baki log fekrele 
Ek gana dale fate break lere 
Jo mei karra hu ha iska bhi Take lele 
Paisa hora transfer 
baki sab cheque lere 
Melody hai gane mei aur tera sirf
Ek layer hai 
Declare hai 
Kitne log fame ke liye bheek lere 
Gane mere barse 
Aur baki sab bheegrele 
Ye log dekhke 
Hum comedy trip lere 
Quality kidhar hai 
Idhar hai 
Jigar 
Bigger hai 
Sufi nasha Chale 
Fikhar hai liquor ka 
Lakda ye kidhar ka 
Harana mushkil hai 
Khudka kuch likhar la 
Public yaha marreli 
Mere ek zikar ka
Teezi mei gaadi hai 
Upper aur dipper kha 
Flex karu sleeper pe 
Full volume speaker ka 
Bantai ki public 
Full Local tu kidhar ka 
Item teri boli bantai boht deeper tha 
Jo daire bhuljata 
Unko mei theekh karta 
Kis kis ko theekh karu 
Aur bhi toh kam hai 
Gussa ara fir bhi bandha boht calm hai
Takleef hori sabko bantai ka naam hai 
Bantai kalam hai 
Rocket bana denge 
Flow 
Tezi mei lo  
Mumbai ka chokra 
Aai changho gho

Pelenge khelenge Inhe
Wanna be ye banenge 
Aur samne ake beta mere 
Strawberry banenga 
Khabri banenge 
Rapper hoke chapri banenge 
Mere jaise banne chahe 
Lekin kabhi ni banenge 
Beta abhi nai milenge 
Mera clock zara fast fast 
Koi ni pass 
Karu blast 
Gana mera
Pehno mask 
Mujhe sas liye 
Bina gane ka man tha 
Sath mere janta Kya
Ukhadega ghanta 
Mujhe Hate karo 
tumhari nai galti 
Agar mei bhi tere jagah hota meri 
Bhi toh jalti
ye bandha kaise jaldi 
Kamaybi leke kalti 
Na parwah mujhe kalki 
Sekhata mujhe galti 
Dalu mere gane beta mahine mei teen char baar 
Seedha teen char war 
Ek dum dhar Mera bar
Meri jaan mujhe mat jaan 
Flow mera maut dega 
 pohchadega shamshan 
Meine bola boht bar sabko 
kam pe dhyan de 
Meine bola zara meri tarah confident reh 
Tu bhi krke dikha meri tarah khudke dum pe 
Baki ek kadam lere 
apun soo kadam pe (x2)

Over pump hai 
beat mera
Flow hai  bombay 

#emiway #bantai #100kadampe

60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. There are two imposters among us again. After lots of band-aids and medbay visits, our friends are back and better than ever, and as usual are hurling through the dark and unforgiving spacescape with nothing but their tiny brains and a maddening amount of terrible arguments. Our group has to figure out who on the ship are murderers, while making sure they are doing their tasks so that their spaceship doesn't continue its forward frontflipping momentum. Is red sus or is blue? Who should we vote out? Which player is the imposter venting to kill? Will people be murdered by the imposter or by their beloved crewmates? Find out in this week's third episode of Among Us but it's a reality show.

snippet.title: First Wash in 44 years! Barn Find Datsun 280z with only 350 Original Miles
snippet.description:
This is the rarest Datsun 280z Barn find ever recorded (as I've been told) with only 350 original miles! It was left in a barn near Hershey Pennsylvania before its first wash in 44 years! You'd expect this to be a complete detailing disaster because it was left untouched for so long...but the paint was in good condition despite being covered in filth and disgusting grime. In this barn find, we use AMMO Frothe to remove the first layer of dust and dirt to ensure the rubber seals did not leak if we power washed. Once confident, we power washed the paint, then compounded and polished with a Rupes polisher during our paint restoration. The Datsun 280z has since won several awards at Zcon and more information can be found at www.350mile280z.com.

snippet.title: Entomologists vacuum Asian giant hornets out of nest found in Whatcom County
snippet.description:
The first Asian giant hornet nest found in the United States appears to have been successfully removed from a tree in Whatcom County, according to the Washington State Department of Agriculture (WSDA). 

Heavily protected crews with WSDA worked to eradicate the nest early Saturday morning. The nest was first discovered Thursday in a tree cavity, about eight feet up, on private property in Blaine. The property owner gave WSDA permission for the nest to be eradicated and for staff to remove the tree if necessary. 

Learn more: https://www.king5.com/article/tech/science/environment/entomologists-safely-remove-first-asian-giant-hornet-nest-found-in-us-in-whatcom-county/281-681e736b-5af2-4101-8a7b-0d2feb6db982

snippet.title: UFC 254 Recap: Khabib stops Justin Gaethje to retain title, announces retirement | CBS Sports HQ
snippet.description:
Justin Gaethje followed through with his gameplan against lightweight champion Khabib Nurmagomedov in the main event of UFC 254. Unfortunately for Gaethje, a good gameplan wasn't enough to beat a perfect fighter. Nurmagomedov scored a win with a second-round submission, unifying his lightweight title with Gaethje's interim championship.

Gaethje said leading up to the fight that he just needed to land solid kicks to the legs of Nurmagomedov to take away the champ's wrestling game and open him up to the challenger's huge power punches. The kicks did land, and Nurmagomedov's legs did seem to be starting to show some damage, but it only takes one moment for Nurmagomedov to put an opponent in a bad position.

After a second-round leg kick from Gaethje, Nurmagomedov drove through a takedown and quickly moved to mount. After locking in a triangle choke, Nurmagomedov rolled to his back and squeezed the choke while Gaethje tapped out. Gaethje's taps were missed by the referee, leaving the challenger unconscious on the canvas.

Following the fight, Nurmagomedov announced his retirement, stating he didn't want to return to the Octagon without his father, who died following COVID-19-related complications earlier this year.

60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. snippet.title: First Wash in 44 years! Barn Find Datsun 280z with only 350 Original Miles
snippet.description:
This is the rarest Datsun 280z Barn find ever recorded (as I've been told) with only 350 original miles! It was left in a barn near Hershey Pennsylvania before its first wash in 44 years! You'd expect this to be a complete detailing disaster because it was left untouched for so long...but the paint was in good condition despite being covered in filth and disgusting grime. In this barn find, we use AMMO Frothe to remove the first layer of dust and dirt to ensure the rubber seals did not leak if we power washed. Once confident, we power washed the paint, then compounded and polished with a Rupes polisher during our paint restoration. The Datsun 280z has since won several awards at Zcon and more information can be found at www.350mile280z.com.

This is the rarest Datsun 280z Barn find ever recorded (as I've been told) with only 350 original miles! It was left in a barn near Hershey Pennsylvania before its first wash in 44 years! You'd expect this to be a complete detailing disaster because it was left untouched for so long...but the paint was in good condition despite being covered in filth and disgusting grime. In this barn find, we use AMMO Frothe to remove the first layer of dust and dirt to ensure the rubber seals did not leak if we power washed. Once confident, we power washed the paint, then compounded and polished with a Rupes polisher during our paint restoration. The Datsun 280z has since won several awards at Zcon and more information can be found at www.350mile280z.com.

snippet.description:
SEVENTEEN (ÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥) 'HOME;RUN' Official MV

ÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥Ïùò Ïù¥Î≤à Ïï®Î≤î ‚Äò; [Semicolon]‚ÄôÏùÄ ÎØ∏Îãà 7Ïßë ‚ÄòÌóπÍ∞ÄÎûò‚ÄôÎ•º ÌÜµÌï¥ Ïù¥ÏïºÍ∏∞Ìïú ‚ÄòÏ≤≠Ï∂ò‚ÄôÏùÑ Ìñ•Ìïú ÏùëÏõêÏùò Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Îã§ÏãúÍ∏à Í≥µÏú†ÌïòÎ©¥ÏÑú Ìïú Î∞úÏßù Îçî ÎÇòÏïÑÍ∞Ä Ïâº ÏóÜÏù¥ Îã¨Î¶¨Îäî Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏóêÍ≤å ‚ÄòÏû†Íπê Ïâ¨Ïñ¥Í∞ÄÎ©∞ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏùò Ìñ•Ïó∞ÏùÑ Ï¶êÍ∏∞Ïûê‚ÄôÎùºÎäî ÎçîÏö± ÏÑ±ÏàôÌïú Í∏çÏ†ïÏùò Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Ï†ÑÌïòÎäî Ïï®Î≤îÏù¥Îã§.

ÌòÑ ÏãúÎåÄÎ•º ÏÇ¥ÏïÑÍ∞ÄÎ©∞ Í≥†Íµ∞Î∂ÑÌà¨ ÌïòÍ≥† ÏûàÎäî Ï≤≠Ï∂òÎì§ÏóêÍ≤å Ïû†ÏãúÎÇòÎßà ‚ÄòÏà® Í≥†Î•º ÏãúÍ∞Ñ‚Äô, ‚ÄòÌï®Íªò ÏõÉÏúºÎ©∞ Ï¶êÍ∏∏ Ïàò ÏûàÎäî ÏãúÍ∞Ñ‚ÄôÏùÑ Î¨∏Ïû•ÏùÑ Ïû†Ïãú ÎÅäÏóàÎã§Í∞Ä Ïù¥Ïñ¥ÏÑú ÏÑ§Î™ÖÏùÑ Í≥ÑÏÜçÌï† Îïå Ïì∞Ïù¥Îäî Î¨∏Ïû• Î∂ÄÌò∏Ïù∏ ‚ÄòSemicolon(ÏÑ∏ÎØ∏ÏΩúÎ°†)‚Äô Ïóê ÎπÑÏú†, ÎèôÏãúÎåÄ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏúºÎ°ú ÏÇ¥ÏïÑÍ∞ÄÎäî ‚ÄúÏÑ∏Î∏êÌã¥‚Äù Í∑∏Îì§Ïùò Í≥µÍ∞êÏùÑ Ï†ÑÌïòÎäî Î©îÏãúÏßÄÎ•º Ïï®Î≤îÏóê Í∞ÄÎìù Îã¥ÏïÑÎÇ¥Ïñ¥ Ï≤≠Ï∂òÎì§ÏùÑ Ïñ¥Î£®ÎßåÏßà Îî∞ÎúªÌïú ÏúÑÎ°úÏôÄ ÏùëÏõê, Í≥µÍ∞êÏùÑ Ï£ºÎäî Ìù¨ÎßùÏùò Ïô∏Ïπ®ÏùÑ Ï†ÑÌïúÎã§.

ÌÉÄÏù¥ÌãÄÍ≥° ‚ÄòHOME;RUN‚ÄôÏùÄ Ïä§Ïúô Ïû•Î•¥ Í∏∞Î∞òÏùò Î†àÌä∏Î°úÌïú ÏÇ¨Ïö¥ÎìúÍ∞Ä ÎèãÎ≥¥Ïù¥Îäî Í≥°ÏúºÎ°ú Í≤ΩÏæåÌïòÍ≥† ÌÉÄÍ≤©Í∞ê ÎÑòÏπòÎäî ÏÇ¨Ïö¥ÎìúÎ°ú ‚ÄòHOME RUN‚ÄôÏù¥ÎùºÎäî ÌëúÌòÑÏù¥ ÏßÄÎãå ÏßúÎ¶øÌï®ÏùÑ ÌëúÌòÑÌïòÏòÄÍ≥†, Î¨¥ÌïúÌïú ÏÑ±Ïû•ÏùÑ ÏßÄÎãå Ï≤≠Ï∂òÏóêÍ≤å ÌûòÏ∞¨ ÏùëÏõêÍ≥º ÏúÑÎ°úÏùò Î™©ÏÜåÎ¶¨Î•º ÏÑ†ÏÇ¨ÌïúÎã§.

SEVENTEEN‚Äôs new album ‚Äò; [Semicolon]‚Äô is an album where they share the encouraging message for the ‚Äòyouth‚Äô like they did in their 7th mini album ‚ÄòHeng:gar√¶‚Äô and also the positive message that ‚Äòwe should all take a break and enjoy the youth‚Äô with the youth that are running towards their goals without any breaks.

‚ÄòSemicolon,‚Äô which is a punctuation mark used when you pause a sentence and then resume again, is used as a metaphor to portray the ‚Äòtime to take a breath‚Äô and ‚Äòtime to laugh and enjoy together.‚Äô ‚ÄúSEVENTEEN,‚Äù as the youth who are living in the same time period as the other youth who are fighting alone and struggling through their lives, uses this metaphor to convey their hopeful and empathic message through the album to comfort and cheer for the youth.

The title song ‚ÄòHOME;RUN‚Äô is a song based on swing genre where the retro-like sound stands out, and it portrays the excitement that the phrase ‚ÄòHOME RUN‚Äô conveys with cheerful and rhythmical sound. It conveys powerful support and comfort to the youth with limitless potentials.

60 Minutes, the most successful American television broadcast in history, began its 52nd season in September. Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.


60 Minutes has won every major broadcast award. Its 25 Peabody and 150 Emmy awards are the most won by any single news program. It has also won 20 duPont-Columbia University journalism awards. Other distinguished journalism honors won multiple times include the George Polk, RTDNA Edward R. Murrow, Investigative Reporters and Editors, RFK Journalism, Sigma Delta Chi and Gerald Loeb awards.

60 Minutes premiered on CBS September 24, 1968. Bill Owens is the program‚Äôs executive producer. The correspondents and contributors of 60 Minutes are Sharyn Alfonsi, Anderson Cooper, John Dickerson, Norah O‚ÄôDonnell, Scott Pelley, Lesley Stahl, Bill Whitaker and L. Jon Wertheim.

snippet.title: Return Home
snippet.description:

Offering hard-hitting investigative reports, interviews, feature segments and profiles of people in the news, the broadcast began in 1968 is still a hit in 2020. 60 Minutes makes Nielsen‚Äôs weekly Top 10 nearly every week and was the #1 weekly television broadcast three times last season.


The program still averages more than 10 million viewers, more than double the audience of its nearest network news magazine competitor. The average audience for a 60 Minutes broadcast is 150% higher than those of the network morning news programs; the audience dwarfs the number of viewers drawn by the most popular cable news programs.  


About a million more people listen to the 60 Minutes radio simulcast in several major cities and on its companion podcast. Tens of thousands each week experience 60 Minutes online. The broadcast‚Äôs segments can be watched at 60Minutes.com and on the CBS All Access app. Its webcast, 60MinutesOvertime.com, offers content originally produced for the web, including behind-the-scenes video about the production of 60 Minutes stories and timely archival segments.


60 Minutes has won every major broadcast award. Its 25 Peabody and 150 Emmy awards are the most won by any single news program. It has also won 20 duPont-Columbia University journalism awards. Other distinguished journalism honors won multiple times include the George Polk, RTDNA Edward R. Murrow, Investigative Reporters and Editors, RFK Journalism, Sigma Delta Chi and Gerald Loeb awards.

60 Minutes premiered on CBS September 24, 1968. Bill Owens is the program‚Äôs executive producer. The correspondents and contributors of 60 Minutes are Sharyn Alfonsi, Anderson Cooper, John Dickerson, Norah O‚ÄôDonnell, Scott Pelley, Lesley Stahl, Bill Whitaker and L. Jon Wertheim.
